{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnmapview\/zoomlevel"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"@property","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" ("},{"kind":"keyword","text":"nonatomic"},{"text":") ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:d","text":"double","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"zoomLevel","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":";"}],"languages":["occ"],"platforms":["iOS"]}]},{"content":[{"text":"Discussion","level":2,"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In addition to affecting the visual size and detail of features on the map,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the zoom level affects the size of the vector tiles that are loaded. At zoom"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"level 0, each tile covers the entire world map; at zoom level 1, it covers ¼","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"of the world; at zoom level 2, ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"1"},{"text":"⁄","type":"text"},{"text":"16","type":"text"},{"text":" of the world, and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"so on.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Changing the value of this property updates the map view immediately. If you","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"want to animate the change, use the "},{"code":"-setZoomLevel:animated:","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" method instead."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The zoom level of the receiver."}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"occ","url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapView\/zoomLevel"},"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/document